# ECC harness (Cursor only)

This rule applies to the **Cursor agent** in repos using this `.cursor` hub. It does **not** configure Alfred/OpenClaw (`openclaw.json`).

## Quick reference

- Docs: `.cursor/integrations/ecc/README.md`
- Skills: `ecc-harness-performance`, `ecc-catalog-consult`, `ecc-continuous-learning`, `agent-harness-security`
- Instincts: `.cursor/hooks/state/instincts/` → session hook may write `active-session-context.md`
- Commands: `/harness-audit`, `/quality-gate`, `/model-route`, `/ecc-consult`, `/loop-start`, `/loop-status`

## Defaults

Prefer `ECC_HOOK_PROFILE=standard`. Use `minimal` if hooks feel heavy. Do not stack a full ECC `install.ps1 --profile full` on this hub.

## Alfred boundary

Bot security: `security-guard` + `alfred-security-skills.mdc`. Do not assume ECC skills in `.cursor/skills/` are loaded by Alfred unless registered in `openclaw.json`.

